      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>Pospisil, Leopold (b.1923) was Curator of Anthropology from 1956-1993. His pioneering research in Papua New Guinea has provided the Yale Peabody Museum with one of its most important ethnographic collections.</p>
         <p>Education</p>
         <p>- Ph.D. Univerzita Karlova v Praze, 1948</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>The archives notably include numerous 35mm slides from L.J. Pospisil's work in New Guinea.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
